1. Adding/Removing Elements
push(item) → Adds an item to the end of the array.
pop() → Removes the last item from the array.
unshift(item) → Adds an item to the beginning of the array.
shift() → Removes the first item from the array.
splice(start, deleteCount, item1, item2, ...) → Adds or removes elements at a specific index.
slice(start, end) → Returns a shallow copy of a portion of the array.

2. Iterating Over Arrays
forEach(callback) → Iterates over elements without returning a new array.
map(callback) → Returns a new array with modified elements.
filter(callback) → Returns a new array with elements that match a condition.
reduce(callback, initialValue) → Reduces the array to a single value.
some(callback) → Returns true if at least one element matches the condition.
every(callback) → Returns true if all elements match the condition.

3. Searching & Finding
indexOf(item) → Returns the first index of the item or -1 if not found.
lastIndexOf(item) → Returns the last index of the item.
includes(item) → Returns true if the item exists in the array.
find(callback) → Returns the first element that matches the condition.
findIndex(callback) → Returns the index of the first element that matches the condition.

4. Sorting & Reversing
sort(compareFunction) → Sorts the array (default is lexicographical).
reverse() → Reverses the array in place.
toSorted(compareFunction) → Returns a sorted copy without modifying the original.
toReversed() → Returns a reversed copy without modifying the original.

5. Joining & Splitting
join(separator) → Converts an array to a string with a specified separator.
split(separator) (on strings) → Converts a string to an array.

6. Combining & Copying
concat(arr1, arr2, ...) → Merges multiple arrays into one.
flat(depth) → Flattens nested arrays up to a specified depth.
flatMap(callback) → Maps each element and flattens the result.

7. Checking & Testing
isArray(value) → Checks if a value is an array (Array.isArray(value)).

8. Filling & Transforming
fill(value, start, end) → Fills elements with a specific value.
copyWithin(target, start, end) → Copies elements within the same array.
